-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Air Arabia, Aramex and Saudi Industrial
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-04-02T12:47:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/persian-gulf-stocks-air-arabia-aramex-and-saudi-industrial.html
Saudi Arabia ’s  Tadawul All Share
Index (SASEIDX)  was little changed at the 3:30 p.m. close in Riyadh after
earlier rising as much as 0.5 percent. The  DFM General Index (DFMGI) 
retreated 0.4 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Air Arabia (AIRARABI)  PJSC advanced 1.1 percent to 72
fils, the highest since March 20. The annual general meeting of
the Middle East’s biggest discount airline is scheduled for
today.  Aramex PJSC (ARMX UH) rose the most in more than a month,
gaining 1.1 percent to 1.79 dirhams. The largest courier company
in the Middle East is also holding an annual general meeting
today.  Saudi Industrial Investment Group (SIIG)   rose to the
highest in more than a week, gaining 0.8 percent to 25.2 riyals.
The investor in petrochemicals projects said it will seek
shareholders’ approval to authorize its board to sell bonds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
